(firstQuint)The Safety and Feasibility of Laparoscopic Total Gastrectomy for Remnant Gastric Cancer.

 A prospective single-arm study designed to further evaluate the of of laparoscopic total gastrectomy for remnant gastric cancer will be performed, to evaluate the safety, feasibility, long-term and oncological outcomes.

 The evaluation parameters are perioperative mobility and mortality, perioperative clinical efficacy, postoperative life quality, immune function and 3-year survival and recurrence rates.

